					<p>Nigeria has Africa’s fastest growing mobile markets and with a 125 percent average annual growth rate in the number of subscribers for mobile and fixed lines, the New statistics from the Information Economic Report (2007-2008), compiled by the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD) reveals that the country is positing itself competitive globally. Nigeria’s telephone subscription figures have climbed to about 45.7 million in the first quarter of 2008 to become Africa’s largest market, overtaking South Africa. (Source: ASNS in West Africa, 05 January 2009)</p>
