<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Tanzania-sugar-sector-to-get-8m-from-EU-in-2009" title="Tanzania sugar sector to get $8m from EU in 2009" alt="link">Tanzania sugar sector to get $8m from EU in 2009</a></h2>

	
					<p>Tanzania will this year access $8 million from the European Union as part of the support programme by the European Union for funding sugar producers. The director of the Sugar Board of Tanzania, Mathew Kombe said the fund is part of the $233 million offered by the EU as an assistance package to 18 countries in the African, Caribbean and Pacific bloc (ACP) for 2007-2017 to address the impact of new lower prices in the European market. (Source: The EastAfrican, Wilfred Edwin, 3 January 2009)</p>
